President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 4 through May 10, 2014, as National Charter Schools Week. In the proclamation, he highlights the importance of a world-class education for every child and recognizes the role that public charter schools play in advancing opportunity. Charter schools have the flexibility to try innovative teaching approaches while adhering to high standards and accountability. Successful charter schools can provide effective approaches for the broader public education system. President Obama calls on states and communities to support high-quality public schools, including charter schools. The proclamation emphasizes the belief that investing in every child will lead to a stronger nation and a brighter world.